<body>
    <h1>Python - Style Guide</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><strong>Page Status</strong>: <span class=3D"status-macro aui-lo=
zenge aui-lozenge-complete">READY FOR REVIEW</span></p>
<p><strong>Creator</strong>: Paul Fry</p>
<p><strong>Version</strong>: 0.2</p>
<p><strong>Date Created</strong>: 21st June 2023</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Here is a Python style guide following commonly accepted conventions and=
 best practices.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-Contents">Contents</h1>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-1.NamingConventions">1. Naming Conventions</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-1.1.CaseStyles,Per-PythonObject">1.1. Case Styl=
es, Per-Python Object</h2>
<p>In summary: </p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li><p>Use <code>snake_case</code><em> </em>for all module, package, functi=
on and variable names.</p></li>
<li><p>Use <code>CamelCase</code><em> </em>for classes.</p></li>
<li><p>Use <code>SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE</code><em> </em>for constants.</p></l=
i>
</ol>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><strong>What is </strong><code>snake_case</code>?</p>
<p>Expand the menu below for more details.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-1622225159" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1622225159" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand fo=
r details</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1622225159" class=3D"expand-content">
<p><code>snake_case</code> combines words by replacing each space with an u=
nderscore (_), and all letters are lowercase, as follows:</p>
<p><strong>Raw</strong>: user login count</p>
<p><strong>Snake case</strong>: <code>user_login_count</code></p>
<ul>
<li><p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://betterprogramming.pub/str=
ing-case-styles-camel-pascal-snake-and-kebab-case-981407998841" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">The following link</a> explains the differences between different cas=
e styles.</p></li>
<li><p>One of the benefits of <code>snake_case</code> is that many of the a=
llowed characters are compatible across S3 and Snowflake.</p></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-CaseStyleSpecification">Case Style Specificatio=
n</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"00f9eb21-6481-40f0-9ccd-c18=
b3fb2dea5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Related to</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Naming Convention</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Module names</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>snake_case</code> (i.e., <code>lowercas=
e_with_underscores</code>)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>lowercase_with_underscores.py</code></p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Package names</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>snake_case</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>lowercase_with_underscores</code></p></=
td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Class names</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>CamelCase</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>ExampleClass</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Function and method names</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>snake_case</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>def example_function():</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Variable names</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>snake_case</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>working_dir =3D os.getcwd()</code></p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constants</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><code>SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE</code> (i.e., <cod=
e>UPPERCASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES</code>)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">PI =3D 3.=
14</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-1.2.AvoidAbbreviations">1.2. Avoid Abbreviation=
s</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Function names, variables and filenames should all be descriptive an=
d eschew abbreviation</p></li>
<li><p>Don=E2=80=99t use abbreviations that are ambiguous to readers outsid=
e your projects</p></li>
<li><p>Don=E2=80=99t abbreviate by deleting letters within a word</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-2.CodeLayout">2. Code Layout</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-2.1.General">2.1. General</h2>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/" re=
l=3D"nofollow">PEP 8 is the official style guide for Python code</a>. It pr=
ovides a set of conventions for writing readable and consistent code. The k=
ey general recommendations are listed below:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Using four spaces for indentation</p></li>
<li><p>Limit lines to 79 characters</p></li>
<li><p>Use blank lines to separate functions and classes</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expand the menu below for further details on these (including examples).=
</p>
<div id=3D"expander-1085737852" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1085737852" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Click to =
expand</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1085737852" class=3D"expand-content">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"02546208-c27c-40fa-9ecd-3fc=
6d4ebe900" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Related to</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Description</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Indentation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use four spaces for indentation (i.e., avoid =
tabs.)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>-</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Line length</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Limit lines to a maximum of 79 characters.</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>-</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Whitespace: imports, classes and functions</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use a newline after imports and before the cl=
ass or function definition.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os
...

from requests import HTTPError


def example_function():</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os
...

from requests import HTTPError
def example_function():</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Whitespace: methods and classes</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Separate methods and classes with two blank l=
ines.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os
...

from requests import HTTPError


def example_function():</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os
...

from requests import HTTPError
def example_function():</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Whitespace: operators and commas</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use a single space around operators and after=
 commas.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">return sh=
arepoint.get_site(host, 'sites/' + site_name.replace(" ", ""))</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">return sh=
arepoint.get_site(host,'sites/'+site_name.replace(" ", ""))</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Whitespace: code readability</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Code <strong>MUST</strong> be spaced logicall=
y to maintain readability.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># Pipelin=
e parameters
src_bucket =3D self.s3_bucket_src
logging.info(f=E2=80=9Dsource_bucket =3D {src_bucket}=E2=80=9D)

target_bucket =3D self.s3_bucket_target
logging.info(f=E2=80=9Dtarget_bucket =3D {target_bucket}=E2=80=9D)</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># Pipelin=
e parameters
src_bucket =3D self.s3_bucket_src
logging.info(f=E2=80=9Dsource_bucket =3D {src_bucket}=E2=80=9D)
target_bucket =3D self.s3_bucket_target
logging.info(f=E2=80=9Dtarget_bucket =3D {target_bucket}=E2=80=9D)</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-2.2.Imports">2.2. Imports</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Import modules on separate lines.</p></li>
<li><p>Use absolute imports whenever possible.</p></li>
<li><p>Avoid wildcard imports (<code>from module import *</code>)<em>.</em>=
</p></li>
<li><p>Place imports in the following order: standard library modules, thir=
d-party modules, and local modules.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>For further details (with examples), expand the menu below.</p>
<div id=3D"expander-1919997398" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1919997398" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Click to =
expand</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1919997398" class=3D"expand-content">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ad4b7f98-5f3a-4e1b-8e5a-0e1=
67bde51b0" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Description</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Import modules on separate lines.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os
import re</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os=
, re</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use absolute imports whenever possible.</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">from pack=
age2.subpackage1.module5 import function2</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">from .sub=
package1.module5 import function2</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Avoid wildcard imports (<code>from module imp=
ort *</code>)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">from math=
 import ceil</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">from math=
 import *</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Place imports in the following order:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li><p>Standard library modules</p></li>
<li><p>Third-party modules</p></li>
<li><p>Then local modules.</p></li>
</ol></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import os=
 # standard modules
import boto3 # third-party modules
import my_local_module # local modules</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">import bo=
to3 # third-party modules
import my_local_module # local modules
import os # standard modules</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-3.Stringformatting">3. String formatting</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-3.1.Usef-strings">3.1. Use <code>f-strings</cod=
e></h2>
<ul>
<li><p><code>f-strings</code> should be used where possible, they provide a=
 clean way to format strings.</p></li>
<li><p>Avoid using <code>str().format</code>.</p></li>
<li><p>Detailed examples of <code>f-strings</code> in action can be found <=
a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://realpython.com/python-f-strings/"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">here</a>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-3.2.StringQuotes">3.2. String Quotes</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Use single quotes for string literals.</p></li>
<li><p>Use double quotes inside strings to avoid escaping.</p></li>
<li><p>Use triple quotes for docstrings and multi-line strings.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expand the menu below for more details, including examples.</p>
<div id=3D"expander-128929914" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-128929914" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Click to =
expand</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-128929914" class=3D"expand-content">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"75a2927a-d488-4a42-9378-05c=
bdfa5ac8b" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Description</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use single quotes for string literals.</p></t=
d>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">print('He=
llo')</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">print("He=
llo")</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use double quotes inside strings to avoid esc=
aping.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">'Sammy sa=
ys, "Hello!"'</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">"Sammy sa=
ys, \"Hello!\""</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use triple quotes for docstrings and multi-li=
ne strings.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">"""
This string is on=20
multiple lines
within three double=20
quotes on either side.
"""</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># This st=
ring is on=20
# multiple lines
# within three double=20
# quotes on either side.</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-4.FunctionandMethodDefinitions">4. Function and=
 Method Definitions</h1>
<ul>
<li><p>Define function parameters without spaces around the equals sign.</p=
></li>
<li><p>Use a single space after the comma in function definitions.</p></li>
<li><p>Place default arguments at the end of the argument list.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expand the menu below for more details (and examples):</p>
<div id=3D"expander-1285066459" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1285066459" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Click to =
expand</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1285066459" class=3D"expand-content">
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5a65315e-2dd9-4ce2-be46-0e2=
c7aca48d0" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Related to</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Description</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Example</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Whitespace in function parameters</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Define function parameters without spaces aro=
und the equals sign.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">func(1, 2=
, axis=3D'x', angle=3D90, size=3D450, name=3D'foo bar')</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">func(1, 2=
, axis =3D 'x', angle =3D 90, size =3D 450, name =3D 'foo bar')</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Whitespace in function definitions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use a single space after the comma in functio=
n definitions.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">func(1, 2=
, axis=3D'x', angle=3D90, size=3D450, name=3D'foo bar')</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">func(1,2,=
axis=3D'x',angle=3D90,size=3D450,name=3D'foo bar')</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Default arguments</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Place default arguments at the end of the arg=
ument list.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">def stude=
nt(firstname, lastname =3D'Mark', standard =3D'Fifth'):</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">def stude=
nt(lastname =3D'Mark', standard =3D'Fifth', firstname):</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Data type declarations</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Use type declarations for method arguments an=
d return values</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><u>Good</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">def get_s=
ecret_by_name(secret_name: str) -&gt; str:

  ...
 =20
  secret =3D &lt;code here&gt;
 =20
  return secret</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><u>Bad</u></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">def get_s=
ecret_by_name(secret_name):
 =20
  ...
 =20
  secret =3D &lt;code here&gt;
 =20
  return s</pre>=20
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-5.CommentsandDocstrings">5. Comments and Docstr=
ings</h1>
<ul>
<li><p>Use inline comments sparingly and keep them concise.</p></li>
<li><p>Use docstrings to document modules, classes, methods, and functions.=
</p></li>
<li><p>Write clear, self-explanatory code and minimise the need for comment=
s.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-5.1.Don=E2=80=99tCaptureChangeHistory/Log">5.1.=
 Don=E2=80=99t Capture Change History/Log</h2>
<div id=3D"expander-1890402230" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1890402230" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand fo=
r more details</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1890402230" class=3D"expand-content">
<ul>
<li><p>The change history SHOULD NOT be stored in the code itself</p></li>
<li><p>Manually maintaining the change history in the code itself is unreli=
able, as it doesn=E2=80=99t show the actual change that has occurred and is=
n=E2=80=99t enforceable</p>
<ul>
<li><p>The change history is captured by the version control system (e.g. G=
it) for each commit that=E2=80=99s occurred. All changes that are pushed to=
 development and production are captured, and diffs of those changes are av=
ailable</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li><p>An example of the anti-pattern that SHOULD NOT be used:</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># Create =
by: Joe Bloggs
# Date: 01-01-2021
# Purpose: Eg transformation script

# Change log:
# Date: 02-01-2021
# Change Made By: Donald Duck
# Change Description: Small change to JSON file read in</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-5.2.Docstring">5.2. Docstring</h2>
<p>All functions should start with a Docstring, explaining <strong>the func=
tion</strong>, <strong>what</strong> it does and <strong>why</strong>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-DocStringFormat:UsereST">DocString Format: Use =
reST</h3>
<p>Use the reST (restructuredText) Docstring format.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><strong>What is the reST (restructuredText) Docstring format?</strong></=
p>
<p>Expand the menu below for more details.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-220323655" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-220323655" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"62ae7df72658117c6ffa7e40d41aa3e7" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Click to =
expand</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-220323655" class=3D"expand-content">
<ul>
<li><p>One of the most prevalent Docstring formats in use today is reST (re=
structuredText).</p></li>
<li><p>Shown below are the main components of the reST Docstring format:</p=
></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">"""[Summa=
ry]
:param [ParamName]: [ParamDescription], defaults to [DefaultParamVal]
:type [ParamName]: [ParamType](, optional)
...
:raises [ErrorType]: [ErrorDescription]
...
:return: [ReturnDescription]
:rtype: [ReturnType]
"""
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>For an overview of the reST Docstring format, see <a class=3D"extern=
al-link" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://sphinx-rtd-tutoria=
l.readthedocs.io/en/latest/docstrings.html" rel=3D"nofollow">https://sphinx=
-rtd-tutorial.readthedocs.io/en/latest/docstrings.html</a>.</p></li>
<li><p>The main components of the reST Docstring format are described below=
.</p></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-6.ControlStructuresandErrorHandling">6. Control=
 Structures and Error Handling</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-6.1.ControlStructures">6.1. Control Structures<=
/h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Use a space after commas in control structures (e.g.,<em> </em><code=
>if</code><em>, </em><code>for</code><em>, </em><code>while</code>).</p></l=
i>
<li><p>Avoid unnecessary parentheses around conditions.</p></li>
<li><p>Use a blank line before a <code>return</code><em> </em>statement if =
it improves readability.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-6.2.ErrorHandling">6.2. Error Handling</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Prefer specific exceptions over catching all exceptions (<code>excep=
t Exception:</code>).</p></li>
<li><p>Use <code>try-except-else</code> blocks when possible.</p></li>
<li><p>Use <code>finally</code> blocks sparingly and only when necessary.</=
p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-7.LintingandAuto-Formatting">7. Linting and Aut=
o-Formatting</h1>
<p>Standard linting and code formatting plugins can be used to maintain cod=
e quality and standardised formatting.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-7.1.Linting">7.1. Linting</h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Code linters highlight syntactical and stylistic problems in your Py=
thon source code, which often helps you identify and correct subtle program=
ming errors or unconventional coding practices that can lead to errors.</p>=
</li>
<li><p>Code linters provide an excellent opportunity to resolve code qualit=
y issues early and often - particularly in scenarios where it isn=E2=80=99t=
 front of mind (e.g., during PoC/MVP development).</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a39faa0d-6a04-4d14-be37-1af=
94356e337" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Pros</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Cons</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Catches easy-to-miss errors like typos, using=
-vars-before-assignment, etc.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><p>Linters aren=E2=80=99t perfect.</p></li>
<li><p>To take advantage of it, sometimes we=E2=80=99ll need to write aroun=
d it, suppress its warnings or fix it.</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-RecommendedLinter:Flake8">Recommended Linter: <=
code>Flake8</code></h3>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://pypi.org/project/flake8/" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Flake8</a>&nbsp;is a popular approach used for linting Python=
 code. It is a standard lint wrapper for Python, where under the hood, it r=
uns three other tools (<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://pypi.org/=
project/pyflakes/" rel=3D"nofollow">PyFlakes</a>, <a class=3D"external-link=
" href=3D"https://pypi.org/project/pycodestyle/" rel=3D"nofollow">pycodesty=
le</a>, and <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://pypi.org/project/mcc=
abe/" rel=3D"nofollow">McCabe</a>) and combines their output.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-7.2.Auto-formattingusingBlack">7.2. Auto-format=
ting using <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://github.com/psf/black"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Black</a></h2>
<ul>
<li><p>Implementing the above styles/coding standards requires proactive ef=
forts from end users.</p></li>
<li><p>Many teams use autoformatters like <a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://github.com/psf/black" rel=3D"nofollow">Black</a> to avoid argui=
ng over formatting.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Python-StyleGuide-8.GeneralGuidelines">8. General Guidelines</h1>
<ul>
<li><p>Use meaningful variable and function names.</p></li>
<li><p>Avoid using mutable types as default arguments.</p></li>
<li><p>Use list comprehensions and generator expressions for concise and re=
adable code.</p></li>
</ul>
